Context Mesh FrameworkOverviewContext Mesh is a framework for maintaining context in AI-assisted software development. It separates Intent (What/Why), Decisions (How), and Knowledge (Patterns) to ensure AI agents always work with complete context.Core Workflow (3 Steps)Intent (Plan): Define WHAT and WHY in context/intent/.Build (Execute): Make technical decisions in context/decisions/ and implement code.Learn (Reflect): Extract patterns to context/knowledge/ and update context.File Structure & Rules1. Intent (context/intent/)project-intent.md: Single source of truth for project goals.feature-[name].md: One file per feature. Must link to its Decision file.Rules:Never implement code without an Intent file.Keep "Status" updated.2. Decisions (context/decisions/)[number]-[topic].md: Architecture Decision Records (ADR).Rules:Create a decision file BEFORE implementing complex features.Link back to the Intent file (Related section).Must include "Context", "Decision", "Rationale", and "Alternatives".3. Knowledge (context/knowledge/)patterns/[name].md: Reusable code patterns or conventions.anti-patterns/: Approaches to avoid.Rules:Check patterns before writing code.If a new pattern emerges, create a file here.4. Evolution (context/evolution/)changelog.md: Track high-level changes to the context/project.5. Agents (context/agents/)Store prompt templates or specific agent configurations here.Operational Rules for AI AgentsPlan, Approve, ExecutePlan: Read Intent and existing Context. Propose changes.Approve: Wait for user confirmation.Execute: Write code, then UPDATE the context files (Status, Outcomes).Bidirectional LinkingFeatures must link to Decisions: - [Decision: Name](../decisions/001-name.md)Decisions must link to Features: - [Feature: Name](../intent/feature-name.md)Definition of DoneCode implemented.Tests passed.Context files updated (Status changed to "Completed", "Outcomes" filled in Decision).Changelog updated.Status Section RequirementsAll Intent and Decision files 